# Copy to .env.local and fill in to enable cloud sync + multi-user.
# Leave unset to run GymLog in single-user, local-only mode (no backend).
#
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL       Project URL — Supabase → Settings → Data API (or the
#                         "Connect" button). Looks like https://xxxx.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY  Your project's PUBLISHABLE key (sb_publishable_...),
#                         shown under Settings → API Keys. This is the renamed
#                         "anon" key and is PUBLIC by design — security comes
#                         from RLS + the PIN-checked functions in
#                         supabase/schema.sql, not from hiding it.
#  ⚠ NEVER use the Secret key (sb_secret_...) here — it bypasses RLS.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
